# Restwell WordPress Theme - Cursor Rules

## Project Context
Migrating a React/TypeScript SPA to a custom WordPress theme.
Source files are for reference only — translate to vanilla PHP/HTML/CSS/JS.
Do NOT introduce React, TypeScript, JSX, or any npm dependencies.

## Project Structure
This is a monorepo. The WordPress theme lives in /restwell-theme/.
The React source for reference only lives in /client/src/.
ONLY ever write or create files inside /restwell-theme/.
Never modify anything in /client/, /server/, /shared/, or /patches/.

## WordPress Standards
- Follow WordPress Coding Standards throughout
- Always escape output: esc_html(), esc_attr(), esc_url(), wp_kses_post()
- Always sanitise input: sanitize_text_field(), absint() etc.
- Enqueue ALL scripts and styles via wp_enqueue_scripts hook in functions.php
- Never inline <style> or <script> tags directly in templates
- Use get_template_part() for reusable components
- Prefix all functions with restwell_ to avoid conflicts

## File Structure
- Template partials go in /template-parts/
- CSS goes in /assets/css/
- JS goes in /assets/js/
- Images go in /assets/images/
- Additional PHP functions go in /inc/ (split logically: enqueue.php, helpers.php, post-types.php)

## HTML/CSS
- Maintain the existing HTML structure and class names from the React source where possible
- CSS variables preferred for colours and spacing
- BEM naming convention for any new CSS classes
- No jQuery — vanilla JS only

## Content Management
- Any hardcoded strings that editors might need to change should become ACF fields
- Use get_field() / the_field() for ACF content
- Always include fallback content if ACF field is empty

## JavaScript
- Preserve existing Map.tsx logic — translate to vanilla JS
- Use wp_localize_script() to pass PHP data to JS (not inline scripts)

## Do Not
- Do not add page builders or Gutenberg block dependencies
- Do not use any WordPress starter themes as a base — build from scratch
- Do not convert class components — these are just HTML templates now
- Do not install any plugins without being asked
